<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hinder2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hinder,</orth> vb. 1) to stop, to obstruct, to keep back; absol.: <cit><quote>of --ing knotgrass made,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.329" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 329</bibl></cit> (stunting). With an accus.: <cit><quote>when his fair course is not --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 7, 27</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 7, 27</bibl> <cit><quote>I am sorry that I have --ed you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 1</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these be the stops that h. study,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed me half a million,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fair hope must h. life's decay,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 4, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that no dissension h. government,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.40" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 40</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>have --ed the passages made toward it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.164" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 164</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>from your affairs I h. you too long,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 54</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to keep back, to prevent: <bibl n="shak. luc 551" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 551</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 71</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.318" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 318</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.6.44" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 6, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.187" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.169" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.335" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 335</bibl>. With <cit><quote>from:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 108</bibl></cit>. With an inf.: <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 34</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>